q("mid251","mid2",C3,"Which of the following drugs is used to treat nasal congestion?",["An alpha-1 agonist (e.g., phenylephrine, oxymetazoline)","A beta-1 agonist","A muscarinic agonist","An alpha-2 agonist"],0,"α1 agonists (phenylephrine, oxymetazoline) → vasoconstrict nasal mucosal blood vessels → decongestant. Prolonged use → atrophic rhinitis (rebound congestion — rhinitis medicamentosa)."),
q("mid252","mid2",C3,"Which of the following results from PROLONGED use of phenylephrine as a nasal decongestant?",["Epistaxis (nosebleed)","Atrophic rhinitis (rhinitis medicamentosa)","Chronic cough","Hypertrophy of nasal mucosa"],1,"Prolonged α1 agonist nasal decongestant → receptor downregulation → rebound congestion → atrophic rhinitis (thinning/atrophy of nasal mucosa). Type C (chronic use) ADR."),
q("mid253","mid2",C3,"A patient taking MAO inhibitors ingests tyramine-rich food (red wine, aged cheese). Which acute response is most likely?",["No significant response","Stimulation of massive NE release (hypertensive crisis)","Inhibition of ACh release","Inhibition of NE release"],1,"MAOIs block MAO → tyramine not metabolized → enters nerve terminals → massive NE release → hypertensive crisis (\"cheese reaction\" or \"tyramine reaction\"). Can be fatal."),
q("mid254","mid2",C3,"Which of the following is a common adverse effect of amphetamines?",["Bradycardia","Somnolence","Constipation","Hypertension"],3,"Amphetamines → indirect sympathomimetics → massive NE/DA release → hypertension, tachycardia, insomnia, anorexia, euphoria. NOT bradycardia or somnolence (those are opposite effects)."),
q("mid255","mid2",C3,"Which of the following drugs can be used to treat hypertension?",["Norepinephrine","Phenylephrine","Alpha-methyldopa","Tyramine"],2,"Alpha-methyldopa is a central α2 agonist → ↓sympathetic outflow → ↓BP. Preferred in pregnancy-induced hypertension. Norepinephrine and phenylephrine RAISE BP."),
